
1️ Advanced Log Analysis
Core Concepts
Log Correlation

Log correlation involves combining logs from multiple sources (firewall, endpoint, authentication, application) to identify attack patterns that are invisible in isolated logs.

Example:

Windows failed login → Event ID 4625

Followed by suspicious outbound DNS traffic

Indicates potential credential compromise or brute-force attempt

Anomaly Detection

Anomaly detection identifies deviations from normal behavior such as:

Logins at unusual hours

Sudden spikes in outbound traffic

Large data transfers from user endpoints

Methods include:

Rule-based thresholds

Statistical baselines

Behavioral profiling

Log Enrichment

Log enrichment adds context to raw logs:

Geo-location of IP addresses

User roles (admin vs user)

Asset criticality

This improves detection accuracy and reduces false positives.

Key Objective

Correlate, enrich, and analyze logs to uncover complex threats and minimize alert fatigue.

